FBIS3-25171 "drafr028_e_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 WEST AFRICA Ghana Government To Review Participation in ECOMOG Force AB0802224094 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in English 1800 GMT 8 Feb 94 AB0802224094 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Ghana Government has decided to review its participation in ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] operations in Liberia if no progress is made to ensure the smooth implementation of peace process within one month. A statement from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs says the government, after a thorough review of the Liberian situation, have expressed disappointment at the lack of progress toward the implementation of the Cotonou Peace Accord which sought to bring peace in the war-torn west African country.
